<h3>Career Relevance</h3>
<div class="card">
<h4>Why Every CM Needs This</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Preconstruction:</strong> Estimators and PMs jointly own the transition from design intent to a fundable number &mdash; the GMP or lump-sum price the owner signs.</li>
<li><strong>Change Order Prevention:</strong> Most costly change orders trace back to a scope item that was never in the estimate, not to a math error.</li>
<li><strong>Owner Trust:</strong> A clean, well-documented basis of estimate with a clear exclusions list is what lets an owner trust a number under a CM at Risk GMP.</li>
<li><strong>Career Path Fit:</strong> Estimating is one of the most common entry points into construction PM careers &mdash; these skills get used weekly for the rest of a CM career.</li>
